						               													<description>Coopolis, the game of cooperatives is the result of our exploration of dynamic and innovative educational resources and has been declared by the Legislature of the Autonomous City of Buenos Aires of Interest in matters of Cooperativism and Education, for its contributions to the dissemination of the values &amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;&amp;#226;&amp;#128;&amp;#139;of cooperation, solidarity and collective work (Declaration no. 148-2014 / File 1043-D-2014).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Coopolis is a creative and dynamic educational game designed to introduce the growing cooperative economy. In Coopolis, players must work together to found and run a democratic company. To develop as individuals and to strive for the success of their cooperative, they must make decisions, while putting their teamwork skills to the test through familiar and entertaining games such as &amp;quot;mimic it&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;taboo&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;draw it&amp;quot;. Yes you can&amp;quot;. This is an exciting game of skill and solidarity, where everyone wins or everyone loses. By playing Coopolis, we learn about the unique benefits, challenges, and how the co-op world works.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
